15/08/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The US Office in Pristina announced Friday (13 August) that career diplomat Philip Goldberg is replacing Marcie Ries as mission chief. Ries’ mandate ended earlier this month. Prior to assuming the post, Goldberg worked as the State Department’s Bosnia and Herzegovina desk officer and was special assistant to Ambassador Richard Holbrooke. His most recent appointment was as deputy chief of mission at the US Embassy in Chile. He also participated in the Dayton peace conference. (US Office Pristina press release, AP, HINA, Tanjug - 13/08/04)
